## 1. Compensating Transaction Patterns

### Core Implementation (Temporal Style)

```java
// Java - LIFO compensation stack
@Override
public void bookVacation(BookingInfo info) {
    Saga saga = new Saga(new Saga.Options.Builder().build());
    try {
        saga.addCompensation(activities::cancelHotel, info.getClientId());
        activities.bookHotel(info);

        saga.addCompensation(activities::cancelFlight, info.getClientId());
        activities.bookFlight(info);

        saga.addCompensation(activities::cancelExcursion, info.getClientId());
        activities.bookExcursion(info);
    } catch (TemporalFailure e) {
        saga.compensate(); // Executes in reverse order
        throw e;
    }
}
```

```go
// Go - Manual compensation tracking
func (s *Compensations) Compensate(ctx workflow.Context, inParallel bool) {
    if !inParallel {
        // LIFO order: undo in reverse of execution
        for i := len(s.compensations) - 1; i >= 0; i-- {
            errCompensation := workflow.ExecuteActivity(ctx, 
                s.compensations[i], s.arguments[i]...).Get(ctx, nil)
        }
    } else {
        // Parallel compensation execution
        selector := workflow.NewSelector(ctx)
        // ... parallel execution logic
    }
}
```

### Execution Flow

```
Success Path:
  Step 1 → Register Comp 1 → Execute Step 1 →
  Step 2 → Register Comp 2 → Execute Step 2 →
  Step 3 → Register Comp 3 → Execute Step 3 → Complete

Failure at Step 3:
  Step 1 ✓ | Comp 3 (skip - wasn't executed)
  Step 2 ✓ | Comp 2 (execute)
  Step 3 ✗ | Comp 1 (execute)
                ↑ Compensation runs LIFO
```

