## 3. Saga Coordination Models

### Choreography-Based (Event-Driven)

```mermaid
Order Service     Customer Service   Order Service
     |                    |                |
     |-- OrderCreated --> |                |
     |                    |-- CreditReserved --> |
     |                    |   or                   |
     |<-- CreditReservationFailed -- |            |
     |                    |                |
  [Approve]           [Reserve]        [Complete]
```

**Pros:** Decoupled, no single point of failure
**Cons:** Cyclic dependencies possible, harder to trace

### Orchestration-Based (Central Coordinator)

```mermaid
[Saga Orchestrator]
       |
       |-- Command: Create Order --> [Order Service]
       |-- Command: Reserve Credit --> [Customer Service]
       |-- Command: Approve/Reject --> [Order Service]
       |
   [Central coordinator manages all steps]
```

**Pros:** Easier to understand, central visibility
**Cons:** Orchestrator is single point, couples logic

