## 4. Error Handling & Fallbacks

### AWS Step Functions Catch Configuration

```json
"Catch": [{
    "ErrorEquals": ["java.lang.Exception"],
    "Next": "RecoveryState",
    "ResultPath": "$.error"
}, {
    "ErrorEquals": ["States.ALL"],
    "Next": "GlobalErrorHandler"
}]
```

### Built-in Error Types

| Error | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `States.Timeout` | Task exceeded TimeoutSeconds |
| `States.TaskFailed` | Task execution failed |
| `States.HeartbeatTimeout` | No heartbeat received |
| `States.Permissions` | Insufficient IAM privileges |
| `States.DataLimitExceeded` | Payload > quota (256KB) |
| `States.ALL` | Wildcard (must be last) |

